eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli caught up with some creatives and brings you this report. #eNCA​ #Dstv403 DURBAN - Artists in Durban are calling for investigations after R300m in relief, meant for them allegedly disappeared. The money was to assist those struggling during the lockdown as they couldn't hold events affecting their livelihoods. Arts and Culture Minister Nathi Mthethwa says an inquiry into the matter is underway. Watch the video above for more on this story.